{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":14822,"record_hash":"sha256:7bfd6992e48a069fd8c2ab4725d57663eb2274e1cf83a550f3e503b4be725335","timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:08:29.106Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Used the Rust review lens and kept this read-only. No files modified; I did not run tests.\\n\\n**Findings**\\n- **P1: CWDs leak into persisted `source_record`.** The parser extracts CWDs for validation, but then stores the full parsed record in `TranscriptRecord.source_record` ([transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:42), [transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:155)). `TranscriptEnvelope::new` persists `redact_value(&record.source_record)` ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:89)), and `cwd` is not considered sensitive ([redaction.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs:42)). That means Codex `payload.cwd` and Claude top-level `cwd` can write local paths like `/Users/...` into GitMeta. POC fix: redact or drop just the known CWD fields after validation, or add exact `cwd` handling to redaction, with tests asserting stored envelopes do not contain the repo path.\\n\\n- **P2: GitMeta appends are likely quadratic for growing transcripts.** `write_capture` calls `set_add` and `list_push` once per record ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:55)). In `git-meta-lib`, each `list_push` reloads existing list entries and re-encodes the full list ([lists.rs](/Users/kiril/.[REDACTED:entropy].rs:72), [lists.rs](/Users/kiril/.[REDACTED:entropy].rs:128)); each `set_add` also re-encodes the set ([sets.rs](/Users/kiril/.[REDACTED:entropy].rs:181)). Appending N records to a long session does repeated full-list/full-set work. POC fix: collect new hashes/envelopes in memory, then write the final hash set and transcript list once with `handle.set(...)` and `git_meta_lib::ListEntry`.\\n\\n- **P2: Idempotent repeat capture still parses the entire stored transcript list.** `write_capture` eagerly calls `read_transcript_hashes_from_list(handle.get_value(...))` before knowing whether any incoming hash is new ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:49)), and that deserializes every stored envelope just to read `record_hash` ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:120)). For a repeated capture of a large unchanged session, this is pure overhead. POC fix: use `record_hashes` as the fast path, and only parse the transcript list when the list is missing, the hash set is missing/stale, or candidate appends require transcript-level dedupe.\\n\\n- **P3: CWD validation repeats filesystem canonicalization for duplicate CWDs.** `ParsedTranscript` stores every CWD occurrence in a `Vec` ([transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:32)), and `validate_cwds` canonicalizes each one ([capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:70)). Agent logs commonly repeat the same CWD many times. POC fix: de-dupe CWD strings before canonicalizing, either in `validate_cwds` with a local set or by storing unique CWDs during parse.\\n\\n- **P3: Redaction clones large records on the hot append path.** `redact_value` clones the full JSON value before mutating ([redaction.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs:8)), and `TranscriptEnvelope::new` does this for every appended record ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:88)). For records with large tool output or message content, this doubles peak memory for the envelope. POC fix: let `write_capture` consume `SessionCapture` or add a `redact_owned_value(Value) -> Value` path so source records can be redacted in place when writing.\\n\\nI did not find a clearly safe “simplify redaction” change beyond the CWD fix. The broad UUID/hex redaction is noisy for Git hashes, but tests currently codify that conservative behavior, so I would only narrow it with an explicit product decision.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:08:29.106Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Used the Rust review lens and kept this read-only. No files modified; I did not run tests.\\n\\n**Findings**\\n- **P1: CWDs leak into persisted `source_record`.** The parser extracts CWDs for validation, but then stores the full parsed record in `TranscriptRecord.source_record` ([transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:42), [transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:155)). `TranscriptEnvelope::new` persists `redact_value(&record.source_record)` ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:89)), and `cwd` is not considered sensitive ([redaction.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs:42)). That means Codex `payload.cwd` and Claude top-level `cwd` can write local paths like `/Users/...` into GitMeta. POC fix: redact or drop just the known CWD fields after validation, or add exact `cwd` handling to redaction, with tests asserting stored envelopes do not contain the repo path.\\n\\n- **P2: GitMeta appends are likely quadratic for growing transcripts.** `write_capture` calls `set_add` and `list_push` once per record ([gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:55)). In `git-meta-lib`, each `list_push` reloads existing list entries and re-encodes the full list ([lists.rs](/Users/kiril/.[REDA